headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid CRL and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: The past six months have been a windfall for Charles River Laboratories’s shareholders. The company’s stock price has jumped 60.1%, hitting $170.64 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
